description: From Ancient Greek μαγειρικός (mageirikós, “culinary”), from μάγειρος (mágeiros, “a cook”) + -ικός (-ikós, “-ic: forming adjectives”).

adjectives.description: magiric (comparative more magiric, superlative most magiric)

entries.meaning: (obsolete, rare) Synonym of culinary: Of or related to cooking.
examples: The magiric science, therefore, began in the year of the world 1656.
